an intraductal papilloma?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Infiltrating cords of cells breaking through the basement membrane","Cystic spaces filled with necrotic debris","Flattened ductal epithelium with surrounding fibrosis","Solid sheets of pleomorphic cells without ductal architecture","Fibrovascular cores with intact epithelial and myoepithelial layers"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe characteristic histological appearance of intraductal papilloma shows \u003Cstrong\u003Efibrovascular cores with intact epithelial and myoepithelial layers\u003C/strong\u003E. These form finger-like projections within the ductal lumen, maintaining a double cell layer pattern typical of benign breast lesions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options represent other breast pathologies:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInfiltrating cords of cells breaking through the basement membrane\u003C/strong\u003E suggests invasive carcinoma\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECystic spaces filled with necrotic debris\u003C/strong\u003E is more commonly seen in comedo-type ductal carcinoma in situ\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFlattened ductal epithelium with surrounding fibrosis\u003C/strong\u003E is characteristic of sclerosing adenosis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESolid sheets of pleomorphic cells without ductal architecture\u003C/strong\u003E is more typical of invasive ductal carcinoma\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe preservation of both epithelial and myoepithelial layers is a key feature that helps distinguish intraductal papilloma from malignant lesions. The fibrovascular cores provide blood supply to the proliferating epithelium while maintaining the overall benign architecture.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Intraductal papillomas are benign breast lesions characterised by finger-like projections within the ductal lumen.","The epithelial and myoepithelial cell layers remain intact in intraductal papillomas, distinguishing them from malignant lesions.","Intraductal papillomas typically arise from the major ducts and can cause nipple discharge."],"references":["Al Sarakbi W, Worku D, Escobar PF, Mokbel K. Breast papillomas: current management with a focus on a new diagnostic and therapeutic modality. Int Semin Surg Oncol. 2006 Jan 17;3:1. doi: 10.1186/1477-7800-3-1. PMID: 16417642; PMCID: PMC1395317.","Tatarian T, Sokas C, Rufail M, Lazar M, Malhotra S, Palazzo JP, Hsu E, Tsangaris T, Berger AC. Intraductal Papilloma with Benign Pathology on Breast Core Biopsy: To Excise or Not? Ann Surg Oncol. 2016 Aug;23(8):2501-7. doi: 10.1245/s10434-016-5182-7. Epub 2016 Mar 9. PMID: 26960929.","Limberg J, Kucher W, Fasano G, Hoda S, Michaels A, Marti JL. Intraductal Papilloma of the Breast: Prevalence of Malignancy and Natural History Under Active Surveillance. Ann Surg Oncol. 2021 Oct;28(11):6032-6040. doi: 10.1245/s10434-021-09870-7. Epub 2021 Apr 19. PMID: 33876349.","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56693"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16233"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56693","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56693"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-17T20:40:04+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-17T20:41:34+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8924"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71219"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"31","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/31"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf97","name":"Oncology","synonyms":[],"description":n